---
description: Reproduce-first, root-cause-only debugging protocol. Apply whenever investigating a bug, error, crash, wrong output, hang, or flaky test, or after any failed fix attempt.
alwaysApply: false
---

Before debugging anything, read and follow `.agents/skills/debugging/SKILL.md` in full,
plus its reference files:

- `.agents/skills/debugging/references/evidence-log.md` — copy this to a `DEBUG_LOG.md`
  scratch file at the start of the session and fill it in append-only as you work.
- `.agents/skills/debugging/references/toolkit.md` — bisection, differential debugging,
  bug-class checklist, flaky-bug protocol.

Non-negotiable core: no fix before the failure is reproduced on demand and the root cause
is confirmed with pasted evidence; one variable per experiment; a regression test that
fails before the fix and passes after; the minimal change that removes the cause — never
a symptom patch (swallowed error, blind retry, bumped timeout, loosened assertion).
